cjminecraft.core.energy.support

Interface IEnergySupport<I>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The interface which represents the container For example IEnergyProvider for support with CoFH energy providers See CoFHSupport
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BuildCraftSupport.BuildCraftHolderSupport, BuildCraftSupport.BuildCraftProviderSupport, BuildCraftSupport.BuildCraftReceiverSupport, CoFHSupport.CoFHHolderSupport, CoFHSupport.CoFHProviderSupport, CoFHSupport.CoFHReceiverSupport, ForgeEnergySupport, TeslaSupport.TeslaConsumerSupport, TeslaSupport.TeslaHolderSupport, TeslaSupport.TeslaProducerSupport

    public interface IEnergySupport<I>
    Used by EnergyUtils to allow integration between different forms of energy storage

      • getEnergyStored

        long getEnergyStored(I container,
                     net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing from)
        Returns how much energy is inside of the energy container
        Parameters:
        container - The container which holds the energy
        from - The side in which the container is acting on (For use with Capability)
        Returns:
        The amount of energy inside the container in the energy unit of the container The unit can received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()

      • getCapacity

        long getCapacity(I container,
                 net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing from)
        Returns how much energy can be stored inside of the energy container
        Parameters:
        container - The container which holds energy
        from - The side in which the container is acting on (For use with Capability)
        Returns:
        The maximum amount of energy the container can hold in the energy unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()

      • giveEnergy

        long giveEnergy(I container,
                long energy,
                boolean simulate,
                net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing from)
        Gives energy to the container. Energy must be in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()
        Parameters:
        container - The container which will receive the energy
        energy - The energy to be given in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()
        simulate - Whether this is a simulation. If so then the energy will not actually be given to the container
        from - The side which the container is acting on (For use with Capability
        Returns:
        The amount of energy that would have been given (if a simulation) or actually given (if not a simulation) to the container in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()

      • takeEnergy

        long takeEnergy(I container,
                long energy,
                boolean simulate,
                net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing from)
        Takes energy from the container. Energy must be in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()
        Parameters:
        container - The container which will have the energy taken out of
        energy - The energy to take in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()
        simulate - Whether this is a simulation. If so the energy will not actually be taken from the container
        from - The side which the container is acting on (For use with Capability)
        Returns:
        The amount of energy which would have been taken (if a simulation) or actually was taken (if not a simulation) from the container in the unit of the container. The unit can be received by calling defaultEnergyUnit()
